page.title: 02Housing in Woking.
page.content: The housing in this block is very varied. In{the south-west kilometre- {square}alone there are four distinct types. To the north: Large detached houses, mainly 1960s; many unmade roads; a few large Victorian houses, two of which are now schools and one an adult education centre. In the centre:Slightly smaller detached houses dating from the 1940s to the 1950s. In the south-west:Quite large terraced Victorian/Edwardian houses; a large modern pub, The Wheatsheaf; a thin sprinkling of light industry; an oak wood, Horsell Moor. In the south-east: A completely different area _ large modern office blocks; a hospital; small terraced Victorian houses with modern infill interspersed with light industry; the McLaren racing car workshop.
